Name: Diffuse_Source
Description: The lucy:Point_Source class presents radiometric conversion constants for converting calibrated pixel values into physical units for resolved/extended sources.

Name: units_of_conversion_constants
Description: For resolved sources, the radiometric conversion produces data in units of radiance. For unresolved sources, the conversion results in units of flux (irradiance). The lucy:units_of_conversion_constants attribute contains the appropriate physical units for the conversion constants in the class in which it is contained to produce either radiance or flux units, as appropriate, when the conversion is applied.

Name: (DN/s)/(erg/cm^2/s/Angstrom)
Description: Units for conversion factors for unresolved (point) sources, to produce units of flux (irradiance).

Name: (DN/s/pixel)/(erg/cm^2/s/Angstrom/sr)
Description: Units for conversion factors for resolved (diffuse) sources, to produce units of radiance.

Name: solar_constant
Description: The lucy:solar_constant attribute supplies the constant to be used for sources with a spectral distribution similar to the Sun to convert calibrated pixel values to physical units.

Name: red_trojan_constant
Description: The lucy:red_trojan_constant attribute supplies the constant to be used for sources with a spectral distribution similar to that of "red" Trojans to convert calibrated pixel values to physical units.

Name: gray_trojan_constant
Description: The lucy:gray_trojan_constant attribute supplies the constant to be used for sources with a spectral distribution similar to that of "gray" Trojans to convert calibrated pixel values to physical units.

Name: dinkinesh_constant
Description: The lucy:dinkinesh_constant attribute supplies the constant to be used for sources with a spectral distribution similar to that of Dinkinesh to convert calibrated pixel values to physical units.

Name: Lucy_Observation_Time_Information
Description: Lucy Mission observation identification and timing information.

Name: observation_id
Description: The Lucy Mission observation identifier.

Name: observation_id_count
Description: The Lucy Mission observation identifier counter. This number increments by 1 with each planned observation sequence (L'LORRI only).

Name: observation_complete
Description: The Lucy Mission observation completion status.

Name: COMPLETE
Description: The observation is complete as planned.

Name: INCOMPLETE
Description: The as-planned observation is incomplete.

Name: UNKNOWN
Description: Available information is insufficient to determine completion status.

Name: observation_missing_packets
Description: The number of missing packets in the observation. The best data quality has no missing packets.

Name: start_sclk
Description: The Lucy spacecraft clock (SCLK) time (in seconds) at the start of the observation.

Name: mid_sclk
Description: The Lucy spacecraft clock (SCLK) time (in seconds) at the mid-time of the observation.

Name: stop_sclk
Description: The Lucy spacecraft clock (SCLK) time (in seconds) at the end of the observation.

Name: mid_utc
Description: The middle time of the observation in ISO UTC format "YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.sss"

Name: mid_sclk_string
Description: The middle time of the observation in Lucy spacecraft clock string partition/SSSSSSSSSS-PPPPP, where S is seconds and P are ticks in units of 1/66535 of a second.

Name: mid_utc_doy
Description: The middle time of the observation in ISO DOY format, YYYY-DOYTHH:MM:SS.sss

Name: mid_utc_jd
Description: The middle time of the observation in Julian day format.

Name: mid_ephemeris_time
Description: The middle time of the observation in ephemeris time, seconds past J2000, TDB.

Name: ccsds_sclk_time
Description: The Lucy spacecraft clock time of the CCSDS playback timestamp in seconds.

Name: Lucy_Observation_Planning
Description: The Lucy Mission observation planning class and attributes describe the observation planning information needed to understand the planned spacecraft observations.

Name: load_identifier
Description: The command sequence load identifier

Name: mission_segment
Description: The Lucy Mission segment

Name: CRUISE 1
Description: The Cruise 1 Lucy Mission segment from date XXXX to date XXX.

Name: CRUISE 2
Description: The Cruise 2 Lucy Mission segment from date XXXX to date XXX.

Name: CRUISE 3
Description: The Cruise 3 Lucy Mission segment from date XXXX to date XXX.

Name: DINKINESH
Description: The Dinkinesh encounter Lucy Mission segment from date XXXX to date XXX.

Name: DONALDJOHANSON
Description: The Donaldjohanson encounter Lucy Mission segment from date XXXX to date XXX.

Name: EGA 1
Description: The EGA 1 (Earth Gravity Assist) Lucy Mission segment from date XXXX to date XXX.

Name: EGA 2
Description: The EGA 2 (Earth Gravity Assist) Lucy Mission segment from date XXXX to date XXX.

Name: sap_identifier
Description: The Lucy Mission science activity plan identifier.

Name: visit_name
Description: The Lucy Mission trojan asteroid visit name.

Name: instrument_side
Description: The Lucy elctronics side.

Name: N/A
Description: Not applicable.

Name: SIDE_1
Description: The "A" electronics side. This is the default electronics side.

Name: SIDE_2
Description: The "B" electronics side. This is the redundant fault protection side used in case of an error on the "A" side.

Name: llorri_status
Description: The status of the L'LORRI instrument.

Name: ACTIVE
Description: The instrument is active.

Name: POWERED
Description: The instrument is powered.

Name: UNKNOWN
Description: The instrument status is unknown.

Name: UNPOWERED
Description: The instrument is unpowered.

Name: lralph_status
Description: The status of the L'RALPH instrument.

Name: ACTIVE
Description: The instrument is active.

Name: POWERED
Description: The instrument is powered.

Name: UNKNOWN
Description: The instrument status is unknown.

Name: UNPOWERED
Description: The instrument is unpowered.

Name: ltes_status
Description: The status of the L'TES instrument.

Name: ACTIVE
Description: The instrument is active.

Name: POWERED
Description: The instrument is powered.

Name: UNKNOWN
Description: The instrument status is unknown.

Name: UNPOWERED
Description: The instrument is unpowered.

Name: ttcam_status
Description: The status of the TTCAM instrument.

Name: ACTIVE
Description: The instrument is active.

Name: POWERED
Description: The instrument is powered.

Name: UNKNOWN
Description: The instrument status is unknown.

Name: UNPOWERED
Description: The instrument is unpowered.

Name: Lucy_Target_List
Description: The Lucy Mission class that contains the target list of potential targets in a given observation.

Name: target_fov_count
Description: The number of possible targets in FOV (SPICE-derived).

Name: target_fov_name
Description: The name of the possible target in FOV (SPICE-derived).

Name: Lucy_Product_Information
Description: The Lucy Mission class that contains attributes specific to the labeled data product.

Name: internal_product_version_id
Description: The Lucy pipeline internal data processing version number. This number is likely to be grater than the PDS version number given in the version_id attribute in the Observation_Area.

Name: LLORRI_Instrument_Parameters
Description: The Lucy LORRI instrument class that contains instrument specific attributes relevant to the labeled data product.

Name: attached_sync_marker_dec
Description: Attached Sync Marker, decimal representation.

Name: attached_sync_marker_hex
Description: Attached Sync Marker, hexidecimal representation.

Name: latch_count
Description: The number of times a latchup has occurred.

Name: calibration_lamp_level_1
Description: The Digital Number (DN) setting for calibration lamp one.

Name: calibration_lamp_level_2
Description: The Digital Number (DN) setting for calibration lamp two.

Name: bias_level
Description: The lucy:bias_level attribute appears in calibrated L'LORRI data products and contains the mean bias level of the detector's dark columns.

Name: read_noise
Description: The lucy:read_noise attribute appears in calibrated L'LORRI data products and provides the CCD read noise for the image.

Name: ccd_gain
Description: The lucy:ccd_gain attribute appears in calibrated L'LORRI data products and provides the CCD gain setting for the image.

Name: bias_offset
Description: The lucy:bias_offset attribute appears in calibrated L'LORRI data products and provides the CCD bias offset between the active and inactive regions of the detector.

Name: frame_transfer_scrub_time
Description: The lucy:frame_transfer_scrub_time attribute appears in calibrated L'LORRI data products and contains the instrument's frame transfer/scrub time. For the L'LORRI instrument, these two quantities (transfer and scrub times) are exactly equal.

Name: LRalph_Instrument_Common_Parameters
Description: The Lucy LRalph instrument class that contains the common (LEISA and MVIC) instrument specific attributes relevant to the labeled data product.

Name: playback_start
Description: Playback science header timstamp of the first m4 packet used in spacecraft clock seconds.

Name: playback_end
Description: Playback science header timstamp of the last m4 packet used in spacecraft clock seconds.

Name: playback_bad_pixel_mask_status
Description: Status of the bad pixel map, true or false

Name: playback_truncation_status

Name: playback_header_type
Description: Playback header type

Name: LEISA_CDS

Name: LEISA_NONCDS
Description: CDS is not used in the current LEISA observation (TBR)

Name: MVIC
Description: MVIC is selected for the current observation (TBR)

Name: OTHER
Description: Other values to be filled in. This is a placeholder.(TBR)

Name: test_pattern_setting
Description: The instrument test pattern setting, 0 is science, 1 is test pattern.

Name: hs_xtrack_start_row
Description: The cross track start row from the high speed header.

Name: scan_row_pixels
Description: The number of pixels in the scan row.

Name: scan_row_pixels
Description: The number of pixels in the scan row.

Name: fpecrc_error_flag
Description: FPE checksum error flag, true or false

Name: m4_calibration_state
Description: Calibration state (TBR)

Name: m4_blackbody_setting
Description: Blackbody state (TBR)

Name: m4_filament_setting
Description: Filament setting (TBR)

Name: fpe_drop_frames
Description: Number of FPE drop frames (TBR).

Name: mce_scan_rate
Description: The MCE scan rate (TBR).

Name: first_packet_timestamp
Description: The timestamp of the first packet recorded in spacraft clock seconds.

Name: last_packet_timestamp
Description: The timestamp of the last packet recorded in spacraft clock seconds.

Name: xsum_error_flag_status
Description: Xsum flag indicating if there are errors in the stored data packet, true or false

Name: lr_acquisition_start_block
Description: The L'Ralph observation acquisition start block address.

Name: mce_start_postion
Description: The MCE start position (TBR), units TBD

Name: mce_end_postion
Description: The MCE start position (TBR), units TBD

Name: board_selection
Description: The instrument side selected

Name: EM1
Description: Engineering Model 1.

Name: EM2
Description: Engineering Model 2

Name: ETU
Description: Engineering Test Unit

Name: FM1
Description: Flight Model 1

Name: FM2
Description: Flight Model 2

Name: blocks_allocated
Description: The number of blocks allocated

Name: LEISA_Instrument_Parameters
Description: The Lucy LRalph LEISA class that contains the instrument specific attributes relevant to the labeled data product.

Name: leisa_mode
Description: LEISA observation mode, T is CDS, F is NONCDS. (TBR)

Name: leisa_observation_allocation

Name: leisa_integration_time

Name: leisa_atrack_start_channel

Name: leisa_atrack_num_channels

Name: leisa_xtrack_start_row
Description: LEISA cross track start row.

Name: leisa_xtrack_num_rows

Name: leisa_offset
Description: LEISA offset (TBR)

Name: leisa_fpa_temperature

Name: mvic_observation_allocation

Name: Point_Source
Description: The lucy:Point_Source class presents radiometric conversion constants for converting calibrated pixel values into physical units for unresolved/point sources.

Name: units_of_conversion_constants
Description: For resolved sources, the radiometric conversion produces data in units of radiance. For unresolved sources, the conversion results in units of flux (irradiance). The lucy:units_of_conversion_constants attribute contains the appropriate physical units for the conversion constants in the class in which it is contained to produce either radiance or flux units, as appropriate, when the conversion is applied.

Name: (DN/s)/(erg/cm^2/s/Angstrom)
Description: Units for conversion factors for unresolved (point) sources, to produce units of flux (irradiance).

Name: (DN/s/pixel)/(erg/cm^2/s/Angstrom/sr)
Description: Units for conversion factors for resolved (diffuse) sources, to produce units of radiance.

Name: solar_constant
Description: The lucy:solar_constant attribute supplies the constant to be used for sources with a spectral distribution similar to the Sun to convert calibrated pixel values to physical units.

Name: red_trojan_constant
Description: The lucy:red_trojan_constant attribute supplies the constant to be used for sources with a spectral distribution similar to that of "red" Trojans to convert calibrated pixel values to physical units.

Name: gray_trojan_constant
Description: The lucy:gray_trojan_constant attribute supplies the constant to be used for sources with a spectral distribution similar to that of "gray" Trojans to convert calibrated pixel values to physical units.

Name: dinkinesh_constant
Description: The lucy:dinkinesh_constant attribute supplies the constant to be used for sources with a spectral distribution similar to that of Dinkinesh to convert calibrated pixel values to physical units.

Name: Radiometric_Conversion_Constants
Description: The lucy:Radiometric_Conversion_Constants class provides the values needed to perform the conversion from the calibrated pixel values to physical units. This conversion is dependent on the spectral distribition of the source, the detector wavelength range, and whether or not the source is resolved. A description of how to convert from data values to physical units is provided in the LLORRI SIS document.

Name: pivot_wavelength
Description: The value contained in the lucy:pivot_wavelength attribute is used when converting L'LORRI calibrated pixel values to physical units.

Name: photometric_zero_point
Description: The lucy:photometric_zero_point attribute supplies the photometric zero point to be used to convert between units of (ir)radiance and visual magnitude, V.
